Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.79,0:00:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Well, the words of today’s text
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.45,0:00:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‎may have reminded you of the admonition
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.26,0:00:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‎at 1 Corinthians 6:18,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.06,0:00:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‎where Paul wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.06,0:00:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“Flee from sexual immorality!”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.17,0:00:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‎or perhaps the words \Nat 2 Timothy 2:22, 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.84,0:00:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,‎where he wrote to Timothy:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.77,0:00:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“Flee from youthful desires.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.38,0:00:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,‎In today’s text,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.38,0:00:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,‎a father is counseling his son
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.95,0:00:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and encouraging him to stay away
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.88,0:00:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,‎from sexual immorality. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.62,0:00:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‎In Proverbs chapter 7, \Nthe counsel is strengthened
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.06,0:00:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‎by means of an experience. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.13,0:00:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The king describes a scene
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.76,0:00:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that he personally witnessed,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.23,0:00:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and we read about it \Nin Proverbs chapter 7, 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.67,0:00:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‎beginning in verse 6. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.67,0:00:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So why don’t we turn there together? 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.34,0:01:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‎At Proverbs 7:6,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,‎you can imagine a father
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.95,0:01:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,‎encouraging a son
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.18,0:01:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and he relates this experience:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.52,0:01:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“From the window of my house,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.59,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“through my lattice, I looked down,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“and as I observed the naive ones
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.29,0:01:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“[or as the footnote says,\Nthe “inexperienced” ones
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.30,0:01:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“—like you, son,\Nthe inexperienced ones],
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.81,0:01:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“I discerned among the youths a young man
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.14,0:01:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“lacking good sense
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.44,0:01:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎[or, “in want of heart,” ftn.].”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.48,0:01:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now, that’s the first strike
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.48,0:01:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,‎against the young man, isn’t it? 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.88,0:01:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‎He’s young and, as a result, 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.82,0:01:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,‎he’s inexperienced\N—the two go together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.19,0:01:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‎But the father proceeds to describe 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.69,0:01:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‎what he observed\Nand the progression of events
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.16,0:01:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that led to a tragic outcome\Nfor the young man. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.17,0:02:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So it says in verse 8
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.24,0:02:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that the young man \N“passed along the street near her corner.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.74,0:02:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now, the “her”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.21,0:02:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‎is a prostitute. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.81,0:02:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‎What is he doing in the neighborhood? 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.52,0:02:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Well, we’re told that “he marched
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.69,0:02:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in the direction of her house.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.69,0:02:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The word “march”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.83,0:02:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‎implies a sense of confidence, doesn’t it? 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.10,0:02:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Isn’t it interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.10,0:02:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that a young person is often confident
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.10,0:02:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‎even in risky situations? 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.67,0:02:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Why? 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Because a young person lacks experience
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.14,0:02:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and can’t always foresee
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.71,0:02:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the implications of a situation
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.92,0:02:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‎or the outcome. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Another factor is highlighted in verse 9:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.66,0:02:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“In the twilight, in the evening, 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.66,0:03:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‎at the approach of night and darkness.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.53,0:03:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So now we have inexperience;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.77,0:03:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,‎we have a bad neighborhood;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.77,0:03:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,‎we have a young man who is confident,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.64,0:03:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,‎who evidently has no intention \Nof committing immorality 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.65,0:03:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and may even feel\Nthat he’s in control of the circumstances; 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.65,0:03:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and it’s nighttime. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.29,0:03:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now, I know as a young man where I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.49,0:03:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,‎everybody knew there were certain places,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.29,0:03:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‎or parts of town,\Nwhere you didn’t go after dark 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.53,0:03:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,‎because it was a recipe for disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.60,0:03:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,‎In verse 10, the inevitable happens. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.91,0:03:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The young man \Nis confronted by a prostitute,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.61,0:03:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and rather than turning around
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and leaving the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.92,0:03:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‎he engages with her in conversation. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.09,0:04:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And in verse 22,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.56,0:04:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‎we read the result
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.59,0:04:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‎—the culmination—\Nof this progression 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.40,0:04:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‎of ingredients: 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.53,0:04:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“Suddenly he goes after her,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.07,0:04:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“like a bull to the slaughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.61,0:04:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‎like a fool to be punished in the stocks.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.81,0:04:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now, what do we learn
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.81,0:04:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‎from this word “suddenly”? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.58,0:04:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Well, simply this:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.62,0:04:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‎In any situation, we can cross a line
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.76,0:04:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‎where we no longer control \Nthe circumstances;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.29,0:04:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,‎rather, the circumstances control us. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And isn’t that what happened \Nto the young man? 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.00,0:04:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,‎He put himself in a situation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.43,0:04:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‎—going down a path
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.47,0:04:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that eventuated, or culminated, 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.61,0:04:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in his committing sexual immorality.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.64,0:04:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And the seriousness of the matter 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.61,0:05:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‎is highlighted \Nin the “b” portion of verse 23, 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.58,0:05:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‎where it says: \N“It will cost him his life.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.45,0:05:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So there’s a ripple effect. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.36,0:05:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Certainly, his relationship \Nwith Jehovah was damaged. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.06,0:05:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,‎His relationship \Nwith his family would be affected. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.13,0:05:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And there are even physical factors
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‎—illnesses that can result
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.00,0:05:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,‎from sexual immorality. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.27,0:05:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now, note in verse 26,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.38,0:05:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the father says:\N“She has caused many to fall down slain,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.75,0:05:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and those she has killed are numerous.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.99,0:05:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And as our Watchtower \Nrecently made the point,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.02,0:05:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‎thousands are disfellowshipped every year
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.73,0:05:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,‎from Jehovah’s family
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.73,0:05:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,‎because of sexual immorality. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.07,0:05:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now, a question \Nthat Brother Kittle addressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.30,0:05:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Is it only the inexperienced
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.61,0:06:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that fall victim to this sad progression? 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.11,0:06:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Well, let’s look at an illustration that appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.48,0:06:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in the Watchtower article. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.48,0:06:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,‎You’ll probably remember this illustration. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.25,0:06:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And here we see two married couples 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.15,0:06:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‎having supper together,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‎a seemingly innocent situation. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.53,0:06:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‎But what are the two folks sitting closest
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.53,0:06:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‎to the camera doing? 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.67,0:06:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‎They’re flirting, aren’t they? 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.70,0:06:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‎You see the sister twirling \Nher hair with her finger,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.37,0:06:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and the brother is saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in essence, ‘I only have eyes for you.’ 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And you can see wedding rings on all four
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.05,0:06:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‎of those individuals’ hands. 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.69,0:06:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‎It’s a start down a slippery slope, isn’t it? 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.03,0:06:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And as portrayed in The Watchtower, 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.03,0:06:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‎this couple \Nwould later accidentally “on purpose” bump
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.20,0:06:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,‎into each other \Nin the parking lot of the Kingdom Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.04,0:07:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,‎after an evening meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.04,0:07:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,‎engage in conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.04,0:07:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and that progressed to texting. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.58,0:07:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now, the good news is,\Nas depicted in The Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,‎these folks realized 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.32,0:07:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that they were headed \Ndown a dangerous path
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.05,0:07:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and took steps to correct it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.09,0:07:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‎But wouldn’t it have been better
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.09,0:07:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‎if they hadn’t gone \Ndown the road to begin with? 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.16,0:07:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,‎It’s a good reminder for all of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.09,0:07:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,‎whatever our age or circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.27,0:07:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Here at Bethel, \Nwe interact with ones of the opposite sex
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.84,0:07:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and many of us are married,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.61,0:07:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,‎but many are not. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.11,0:07:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,‎But as we were reminded,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‎we want to make sure our conduct is chaste 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.45,0:07:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and pleasing to Jehovah. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.39,0:07:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‎The same holds true at the Kingdom Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and in our use of the Internet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.99,0:07:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and in our choice of entertainment. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.96,0:08:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,‎We don’t want to start down a path
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.40,0:08:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that could take us away from Jehovah. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.20,0:08:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,‎I’ll never forget a pioneer sister
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.94,0:08:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‎who used to counsel us young people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.21,0:08:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in the congregation, and we loved her. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,‎But she had an expression \Nthat she would tell us,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.05,0:08:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,‎“If you’re not going to burn down the barn,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.19,0:08:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‎don’t strike the match.” 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.56,0:08:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Now, what’s the point of her statement? 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.29,0:08:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Why start a progression of events
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.70,0:08:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,‎that we know will lead \Nto sadness and tragedy? 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.40,0:08:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So we don’t even go there. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.47,0:08:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,‎And even if we’re inexperienced, \Nwe can act wisely. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.11,0:08:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‎What did the psalmist say? 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.44,0:08:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,‎He said: ‘How can a young man \Nkeep his path clean? 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,‎‘By keeping on guard
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.12,0:08:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‎according to Jehovah’s word.’ 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.35,0:08:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So Jehovah has given us everything we need
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.65,0:09:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎to remain clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.59,0:09:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,‎So talk to Jehovah about it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.59,0:09:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Be alert to identify and be determined
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.70,0:09:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‎to avoid dangerous situations,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‎and then we don’t have to experience 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.20,0:09:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,‎the sad outcome \Nof the young man described
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in Proverbs chapter 7. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.71,0:09:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‎Instead, we can succeed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.98,0:09:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,‎in fleeing from sexual immorality.
